result.adr_address: G/F, 93 Catchick St, Kennedy Town, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: G/F, 93 Catchick St, Kennedy Town, Hong Kong
result.name: Mama Malouf

reviews.text:
Pretty pricey for a neighborhood joint, but then this is Hong Kong.

Most of the food’s actually pretty faultless - best to go on Mondays when mains are 2-for-1, which is pretty awesome value. 

The cauliflower, chicken skewers, and the sea bass on rice is fantastic.

Good for: Monday dinner, weeknight dinner

The food is okay, but they try to fit too many turnovers for each table. Low corkage fee and pretty good food, but nothing amazing. And you have to go outside for the restroom which isn't ideal for when it's raining.
Decent food. Overpriced and terrible service. Get some waiters that don’t scowl and take guests food away without asking. Pathetic.

I was in the restaurant. I asked for a falafel wrap that they can only make if you order online... 

This is the most petty thing I have hear about in Hong Kong restaurants! 

Even the manager couldn’t resolve such a simple problem. 

They make the falafel wraps in the same kitchen as the online food! 

How difficult is it to serve the customers who are sitting in your restaurant? 

This is disappointing and ruined the whole experience before it even started.

The waiter was not polite where they do the char Chan teng style taking the dishes without asking, where some toppings left from the squid.
Then we have the beef skewers also the sauce was taken away while the beef yet is about to finish.
As for the shish was a little too slaty and dry best part is they serve with some sauce taste like mayo!
